Description: Pine Mountain Brand team has understood the powerful urge to gather close around the warmth of the hearth.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Since their passion for fire began, Pine Mountain Brand team has understood the powerful urge to gather close around the warmth of the hearth. Fire feeds their soul and warms their spirit. So we’ve made it their mission to bring you nature-inspired products that make it easy to nestle up to a cozy fire, in the fireplace or around the campfire, with a simple strike of a match. Their story begins in 1980, when their team developed its first Firestarter products. Knowing that starting a fire was often the greatest challenge, making the task simple—and fast—seemed a great place to bring fresh ideas. Not only did They create an easy way to start a fire using all-natural American hardwood sawdust, but They also found a way to utilize a previously unused resource. Inspiration and momentum really began to percolate when They saw coffee houses popping up around the country, yielding another previously unused resource: coffee grounds. The aroma of brewed coffee is nirvana, so why not bring two great experiences—gathering around a hearth and the smell of fresh coffee—into one? In 1999 the Java-Log® Firelog was born. And just four years later it was named one of TIME® magazine’s Best Inventions of the Year. Innovation didn’t stop there. A source of beauty and joy, fire delights the senses with its crackling notes and rich, vibrant hues. Inspired by this realization, their Cracklelog® and ColorCrackle® offerings were introduced, doubly enhancing the evocative pleasures of a good fire.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle, Food and Beverage, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment
